00:00:20.840 --> 00:00:21.840
1.

00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:22.840
What You See Is What You Get

00:00:22.840 --> 00:00:28.770
Older dogs are open books - from the start,
you'll know important things like their full-grown

00:00:28.770 --> 00:00:34.060
size, personality and grooming requirements.

00:00:34.060 --> 00:00:51.010
All this information makes it easier to pick
the right dog and forge that instant love

00:00:51.010 --> 00:00:55.500
connection that will last a lifetime.

00:00:55.500 --> 00:01:06.640
If you're not so into surprises, an older
dog is for you!

00:01:06.640 --> 00:01:07.680
2.

00:01:07.680 --> 00:01:08.680
Easy to Train

00:01:08.680 --> 00:01:09.680
Think you can't teach an old dog new tricks?

00:01:09.680 --> 00:01:10.680
Hogwash!

00:01:10.680 --> 00:01:11.680
Older dogs are great at focusing on you - and
on the task at hand - because they're calmer

00:01:11.680 --> 00:01:12.680
than youngsters.

00:01:12.680 --> 00:01:13.680
Plus, all those years of experience reading
humans can help them quickly figure out how

00:01:13.680 --> 00:01:14.680
to do what you're asking.

00:01:14.680 --> 00:01:15.680
3.

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:16.680
Seniors are Super-Loving

00:01:16.680 --> 00:01:17.680
One of the cool parts of the SPCA staff job
is reading stories from people just like you

00:01:17.680 --> 00:01:18.680
who have opted to adopt.

00:01:18.680 --> 00:01:19.680
The emails they get from pet parents with
senior dogs seem to all contain beautiful,

00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:20.680
heartfelt descriptions of the love these dogs
give you - and those of you who adopted dogs

00:01:20.680 --> 00:01:21.680
already in their golden years told them how
devoted and grateful they are.

00:01:21.680 --> 00:01:22.680
It's an instant bond that cannot be topped!

